(166, 2, 'The missing neutrinos had changed flavor during their journey from the sun, making them invisible to detectors calibrated for only one type.'),
(166, 3, 'Improved detector technology revealed that earlier instruments had systematically undercounted the neutrinos reaching Earth.'),
(166, 4, 'Physicists determined that neutrinos were being absorbed by the Earth''s magnetic field before they could reach underground detectors.'),
(167, 1, 'It would settle a long-standing personal rivalry between competing research teams in Japan and Canada.'),
(167, 2, 'It is necessary primarily for improving the efficiency of nuclear power plants that rely on neutrino-based energy conversion.'),
(167, 3, 'It is essential for refining cosmological models that describe how the large-scale structure of the universe formed and evolved.'),
(167, 4, 'It would enable scientists to develop practical applications of neutrino beams for long-distance communication.'),
(168, 1, 'confirmed predictions that had already been incorporated into the Standard Model decades earlier'),
(168, 2, 'was largely anticipated by the scientific community and therefore generated little immediate interest'),
(168, 3, 'applied only to a narrow subset of neutrino interactions and had limited theoretical significance'),
